5:
Is that all of 'em? I swear the report
we got said there'd be more.
9:
There might be other groups waiting
out there. After we catch our
breaths, we should have a look
around.
13:
Good work, everyone! I've got cold
towels for you all!
20:
But, uh, Millet? You don't have to do
this kinda stuff for us.
25:
It's fine! I'm not much use in battle,
so the least I can do is give you the
best support possible!
31:
Just support? Pretty sure that
adventurer you look up to does
more than that, doesn't she?
40:
...Sorry, forget I said anything. I spoke
outta line there.
56:
Third volume? That's the one that
has Patty fighting for the first time,
right?
65:
Yep, the whole series. Started it out
of curiosity, then got sucked in really
quickly.
70:
The same goes for me. I was
especially impressed with the
depiction of the fight against the
great dragon. It was very realistic.
74:
Patty played a big role in that fight,
huh? She didn't do much in the first
half, but she totally stole the show in
the second.
79:
Yeah, that's right! She wasn't used to
fighting, but she took up the sword
anyway to protect her friends—
94:
I wanted so much to be like Patty,
but I... I only...
112:
I'll hold this position! You need to
lead everyone else to safety!
132: I can do this... I'm an adventurer now!
144:
We were all saved, thanks to you.
Truly, from the bottom of our
hearts... Thank you!
147:
See? You've got some fight in you
after all. Great job back there.
151: I-I guess I do... I really did it, huh?
154:
U-um, could we spend more time
doing combat training?
156:
I... I really want to get better at
fighting!
161: You don't even need to ask!
168:
...Ah, Alk, the ends of your shirt are
frayed.
172:
Huh? I totally didn't notice. I'll have to
fix that later.
175:
That's okay, I can take care of it right
now! I always carry around my
sewing kit.
184:
Well, like I said from the very
beginning...
188:
I want to be an adventurer who can
fight AND support the party!
